// Sentry DSN build setting.
//
// Default is EMPTY: repo builds ship with remote crash reporting fully
// disabled, even if a user flips the opt-in toggle. To enable uploads for
// your own signed builds, drop your DSN into Config/Sentry.local.xcconfig
// (gitignored) — see Config/Sentry.local.xcconfig.example.
//
// IMPORTANT: store the DSN WITHOUT its "https://" scheme. xcconfig treats
// "//" as a comment, so a full "https://…" value gets truncated. The rest
// of a DSN has no "//", so the schemeless form is safe; CrashReporting
// re-adds "https://" at runtime. Example:
//
//   SENTRY_DSN = examplePublicKey@o0.ingest.sentry.io/0

SENTRY_DSN =

// Optional local override (gitignored). The "?" makes the include silent
// when the file is absent, so clean checkouts still build.
#include? "Sentry.local.xcconfig"
